  abstract = {We replicate the empirical results in Section 4 of Alvarez et al. (2022). First, we were able to reproduce the original authors’ major empirical results, but only after editing the program for it to run on our computing platform. There are small discrepancies in the empirical estimates, e.g. bootstrapped standard errors, that involve the use of simulations. Second, we replicated Alvarez et al.’s results by adopting the data cleaning criteria used by their original data source (Cavallo 2018) to evaluate its robustness to data handling procedures. We found noticeable changes in the empirical results that can have important implications on the effects of monetary policy. To conclude, we propose using Docker container to promote research reproducibility, and more attention is needed on data handling to improve the robustness of empirical research.},
