  abstract = {Hoopes et al., (2021) analyze United States tax return data encompassing all individual taxable stock sales between 2008 and 2009, to investigate the individuals who increased their stock sales in response to market turbulence. Our findings reveal that such increases were notably prevalent among investors in the highest tiers of the income distribution, including the top 1% and 0.1%, as well as retirees and those at the uppermost levels of the dividend income distribution. We reproduce the paper’s main findings and results are very similar.},
